1. Turing Test Implementation Architecture

The Turing Test evaluates whether a machine can behave like a human in conversation.

Architecture Components
1. User Interface

A chat interface where a human judge communicates with two participants:

Human participant

AI system

The judge does not know which is which.

2. Conversation Manager

Handles message routing between:

Judge

AI agent

Human participant

3. AI Response Generator

The AI system processes the judge’s queries and produces responses using:

Natural Language Processing (NLP)

Knowledge base

Dialogue model

4. Human Participant Module

Another human answers the same questions independently.

5. Evaluation Module

After several interactions, the judge decides which participant is human.

If the judge cannot reliably distinguish the AI, the system is said to pass the Turing Test.

